        <!-- Lessons Learned -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-secondary mb-6">Continuous Improvement Culture</h3>

          <div class="bg-surface border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4">Key Lessons from Major Incidents</h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-bold text-secondary mb-3">Technical Systems</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
                  <li>• Redundancy in critical flight control systems</li>
                  <li>• Pilot understanding of automated systems</li>
                  <li>• Robust failure mitigation strategies</li>
                  <li>• Comprehensive system documentation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-bold text-secondary mb-3">Human Factors</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
                  <li>• Pilot mental health screening and support</li>
                  <li>• Enhanced crew resource management</li>
                  <li>• Threat and error management training</li>
                  <li>• Open safety reporting culture</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="pull-quote">
            &#34;The aviation industry&#39;s commitment to learning from tragedies and implementing continuous improvements has created a resilient system where multiple layers of defense prevent errors from escalating into accidents.&#34;
          </div>

          <p class="text-muted mb-6">
            This culture of continuous improvement is sustained through rigorous accident investigation processes, widespread adoption of Safety Management Systems (SMS), and proactive analysis of operational data. The industry&#39;s commitment to sharing safety information and best practices across airlines, manufacturers, and regulatory bodies creates a global safety net.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Future Challenges -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-secondary mb-6">Emerging Challenges and Future Priorities</h3>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
            <div>
              <img src="https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/www.aerospacemanufacturinganddesign.com/faf469c00805c9734ed60fbbb7a264346ed7fa29.jpg" alt="Urban Air Mobility vehicle flying over cityscape" class="w-full h-48 object-cover rounded-lg mb-4" size="medium" aspect="wide" style="photo" query="urban air mobility vehicle flying over city" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" data-modified="1" data-score="11598.00"/>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">New Airspace Integration</h4>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                The integration of Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS) and Urban Air Mobility (UAM) vehicles presents complex challenges for safe separation, diverse vehicle performance management, and automated traffic solutions.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted">
                <li>• Detect-and-avoid technologies</li>
                <li>• Automated traffic management</li>
                <li>• Clear rules of the air</li>
                <li>• Regulatory framework development</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Climate Change Impact</h4>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                Climate change is expected to increase the frequency and intensity of severe weather events, requiring improved forecasting, resilient aircraft designs, and enhanced pilot training for extreme conditions.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted">
                <li>• Increased turbulence events</li>
                <li>• Thunderstorm intensity</li>
                <li>• High wind conditions</li>
                <li>• Weather forecasting improvements</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="bg-surface border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4">Cybersecurity Priorities</h4>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                As aircraft and ATC systems become increasingly digital and interconnected, cybersecurity vulnerabilities require continuous investment in security measures, threat detection, and incident response capabilities.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-shield-alt text-accent"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">System resilience against cyber threats</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-eye text-accent"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">Continuous threat detection</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-bolt text-accent"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">Rapid incident response</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4">Sustainability Initiatives</h4>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                Development of Sustainable Aviation Fuels (SAFs) and new propulsion technologies will introduce new safety considerations that need proactive addressing.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-leaf text-green-500"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">Sustainable Aviation Fuels</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-battery-full text-green-500"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">Electric propulsion systems</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                  <i class="fas fa-tint text-green-500"></i>
                  <span class="text-sm">Hydrogen-powered aircraft</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-700 mb-3">Workforce Development</h4>
            <p class="text-blue-600 mb-4">
              Maintaining a skilled and proficient workforce, including pilots, air traffic controllers, and maintenance personnel, will be crucial for addressing technological advancements and evolving operational demands.
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <div class="text-center">
                <i class="fas fa-user-graduate text-2xl text-blue-500 mb-2"></i>
                <p class="text-sm font-bold">Continuous Training</p>
